{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/head-injury/goals-outcome-measures/nice-quality-standards/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"04a64b49-1bfc-5ccc-b972-367a10a3d60c","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field fcb7cfb1-cb16-4eaa-a9da-8fe5448980f6 --><h2>NICE quality standards</h2><!-- end field fcb7cfb1-cb16-4eaa-a9da-8fe5448980f6 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 09a014e1-2950-4560-9394-d91a2f972f94 --><!-- begin field eb71d5a9-53a9-4c28-907b-c740e5536757 --><p><strong>The following National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) quality standards have been identified for head injury, which are relevant for primary care:</strong></p><ul><li>Statement 1. People attending an emergency department with a head injury have a CT head scan within 1 hour of a risk factor for brain injury being identified.</li><li>Statement 2. People attending an emergency department with a head injury have a CT head scan within 8 hours of the injury if they are taking anticoagulants but have no other risk factors for brain injury.</li><li>Statement 3. People attending an emergency department with a head injury have a CT cervical spine scan within 1 hour of a risk factor for spinal injury being identified.</li><li>Statement 4. People attending an emergency department with a head injury have a provisional written radiology report within 1 hour if a CT head or cervical spine scan is performed.</li><li>Statement 5. People with a head injury who have a Glasgow Coma Scale (GCS) score of 8 or lower at any time have access to specialist treatment from a neuroscience unit.</li><li>Statement 6. People who are in hospital with new cognitive, communicative, emotional, behavioural, or physical difficulties that continue 72 hours after a traumatic brain injury have an assessment for inpatient rehabilitation.</li><li>Statement 7. Community-based neurorehabilitation services provide a range of interventions to help support people (aged 16 and over) with continuing cognitive, communicative, emotional, behavioural, or physical difficulties as a result of a traumatic brain injury.</li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/head-injury/references/\">NICE, 2014b</a>]</p><!-- end field eb71d5a9-53a9-4c28-907b-c740e5536757 --><!-- end item 09a014e1-2950-4560-9394-d91a2f972f94 -->","topic":{"id":"9c82c71c-776b-5830-a9b5-f2a1f6e35152","topicId":"22e7906b-f704-4d08-a97c-ab54e669323e","topicName":"Head injury","slug":"head-injury","lastRevised":"Last revised in July 2016","chapters":[{"id":"36484ef0-87eb-5854-8fc9-13ff9e51cd78","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"a7070078-af1b-59a5-a752-8e5e04278465","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"8fdc6898-f17a-5206-ae63-22888799fa23","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"dd05f53c-9e78-5093-955c-34fc3983198b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"18750411-4e80-5f36-987b-228e2d67354c","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"9af40024-874c-5272-93d0-6d40a04c0a49","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"ce894088-4f08-53d3-b4e0-ce8a765c1dd4","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"8dcefa1c-0e26-5c37-ba8b-0e73706e501e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"840e3ede-e526-5282-a63f-af07547e24e4","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"7cab23d8-916a-5694-9eef-78887f368d1f","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"6a9d6f45-556a-5ade-9ff6-d32d2f7a5bb7","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"04a64b49-1bfc-5ccc-b972-367a10a3d60c","slug":"nic